Midgaard's High Archive has flagged active Ash Cult forward positions in the Western Fold Approach as the primary obstacle to any authorized expedition into the deeper Cinderteeth zones. Forward zealots are maintaining active patrol coverage of the approach corridor and intercepting everything that enters the zone without cult markings. Six kills will disrupt the patrol rotation sufficiently for High Archive expedition teams to make supervised entry attempts.
Six ash cult forward zealot kills are logged and Midgaard's High Archive expedition coordinator reports that the patrol coverage on the approach corridor has thinned to sporadic presence. The first supervised entry team has been cleared to proceed. The Archive notes that the zealots maintained a surprisingly orderly withdrawal pattern, suggesting the deeper Cult leadership was informed of your engagement before you reached the outer patrol line.
